<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,249,562]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,249,274]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Comments.</emphasis>
Several issues surround the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[700,831,250,273]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[700,831,250,273]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Ceramaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including uncertainty regarding its monophyly and overlap with such genera as 
<taxonomicName authority="Mah 2011" authorityName="Mah" authorityYear="2011" box="[469,712,285,310]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Peltaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[469,570,285,310]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Peltaster</emphasis>
(Mah 2011)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,249,562]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
I argue that species described herein most closely resembles the type species, 
<taxonomicName box="[1069,1236,321,346]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="grenadensis">
<emphasis box="[1069,1236,321,346]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">C. grenadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and share several fundamental synapomorphies, including the presence of wide (W&gt;L) inferomarginal plates, strongly abactinal facing superomarginal plates, and a flattened, pentagonal body shape (R/r&lt;2.0). These characters serve to separate 
<emphasis box="[151,779,429,454]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName box="[151,251,429,454]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="clarki">C. clarki</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[261,430,429,454]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="grenadensis">C. grenadensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[441,585,430,453]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="japonicus">C. japonicus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[595,779,429,454]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="leptoceramus">C. leptoceramus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[791,892,429,454]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="smithi">
<emphasis box="[791,892,429,454]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">C. smithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[945,1097,430,453]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="pointsurae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[945,1097,430,453]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">C. pointsurae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1103,1165,429,454]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1103,1165,429,454]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[1233,1423,429,454]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Bathyceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="118" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[1233,1423,429,454]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Bathyceramaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,249,562]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
Descriptions of some 
<taxonomicName box="[451,583,466,489]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[451,583,466,489]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Ceramaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., including 
<taxonomicName authority="McKnight 1993" authorityName="McKnight" authorityYear="1993" box="[756,1168,465,490]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="glasbyi">
<emphasis box="[756,979,465,490]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Ceramaster glasbyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="McKnight" box="[988,1168,465,490]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" refString="McKnight, D. G. (1993) Records of echinoderms (excluding holothurians) from the Norfolk Ridge and Three Kings Rise north of New Zealand. New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 20, 165 - 190." type="journal article" year="1993">McKnight 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
display a more stellate shape and lack fasciolar grooves. These will need to be considered more thoroughly pending an overview of the 16 species nominally assigned to 
<emphasis box="[491,628,538,561]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName box="[491,624,538,561]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Ceramaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Ceramaster</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
